description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Theatre Staff &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;University Hospitals Dorset NHS Foundation Trust &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 Vacancies: Clinical Team Leader - TACT team support – Main Theatres - Trauma&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operating Department Practitioners, Anaesthetic Nurses or Registered Nurses &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are are working to develop an expanded service for the Dorset community and wider areas. Poole is a great place to live and work where patient care and staff welfare are our top priorities. We are located in Poole town centre near the coast and New Forest. All this is on offer to any nursing and theatre practitioners making their next career move.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At this exciting time, are you what we are looking for?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With the management team in place and focus on quality, transformation and service development, we are increasing our operating theatre suite and are looking for motivated people, to join our expanding theatre department delivering a 24 hour service and working across sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer great opportunities with an extensive educational program, to include the development of Surgical First Assistants (SFA), Assistant Theatre practitioners, nurse associates, leadership and management development to name but a few.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We pride ourselves on our friendly working environment and our desire to lead on Best Practice in the Operating Theatre setting. If you have the knowledge, skills, experience and drive that we are looking for to join our friendly and supportive team, then Poole Hospital theatres is the place for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working with multi professional colleagues, you will have post qualification experience, working in an operating theatre setting across different specialities – with your core team being in the Orthopaedic trauma theatres. Other areas within the theatre department are, gynaecology, head and neck, obstetrics, general surgery, anaesthetics and recovery– and you will become a valued member of the team across sites. We encourage duel or multi skilled practitioners, however full training will be given to facilitate development. Your peers, Anaesthetists, surgeons and senior staff will support you to learn new skills and to expand your practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Registered Operating Department Practitioner, Registered Nurse or Registered Nurse with a recognised anaesthetic course, who has experience across a range of different specialties with an interest in trauma&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note: if this job requires you to have a DBS check to enable you to properly fulfil the requirements of the job, on appointment you will be required to repay the cost of obtaining a DBS check and this amount will be reclaimed from your salary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 12/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provisional interview date: week commencing 23/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;INFORMAL VISITS ARE MOST WELCOME AND ENCOURAGED&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details or to arrange a visit please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jenny Miller, Clinical Team Manager Trauma&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;jenny.miller@uhd.nhs.uk - 0300 019 2405&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
